## Query Optimization

### select (Limit Columns)

```ruby
# Load only specific columns
Article.select(:id, :title, :created_at)

# With association
Article.includes(:user).select('articles.*, users.name as author_name')

# Count without loading records
Article.select('COUNT(*) as count').first.count
```

### pluck (Get Array of Values)

```ruby
# Get array of single column
Article.pluck(:title)
# => ["Article 1", "Article 2", "Article 3"]

# Multiple columns (returns array of arrays)
Article.pluck(:id, :title)
# => [[1, "Article 1"], [2, "Article 2"]]

# More efficient than map
Article.pluck(:title)           # Good - single query
Article.all.map(&:title)        # Bad - loads all records first

# Get IDs
Article.where(status: 'published').pluck(:id)
```

### ids (Get Array of IDs)

```ruby
# Get array of IDs (optimized pluck(:id))
Article.ids
Article.where(status: 'published').ids
# => [1, 2, 3, 4, 5]
```

### exists?

```ruby
# Check if record exists (efficient)
Article.where(slug: 'my-article').exists?  # Returns true/false
Article.exists?(slug: 'my-article')        # Shorter syntax

# More efficient than:
Article.where(slug: 'my-article').any?     # Loads records
Article.where(slug: 'my-article').present? # Loads records
```

